    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Describe your issue\n\ni.e. should be enable it on 3.2.x as well as just master?",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I think it'd be helpful to keep the build environment of the 3.2 branch (and later actively maintained branches) up to date. As long as the PRs build fine, there's little risk of breaking anything.\n\nI've updated the config in master (that's supposedly enough).\n\nI'm not sure how easy it will be to merge the maintenance branch back into the master branch if both are maintained by dependabot, but I'd guess that we'd get away with empty (`-s ours`) merges most of the time.",
