        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> We could split the dependabot config to get separate PRs for the risky dependencies, which is currently only `cibuildwheel`, I think. That would simplify the updates of everything else.\n\nI'd argue `setuptools`, `twine` and maybe `abi3audit` should also be considered \"risky\" since they're used by the wheelbuilder action too. They're currently installed from `pip install` in a script with no version pinning.",
